# Subdirectory Index

Welcome to the test subdirectory! This demonstrates how Gemini servers handle directory indexing.

## Directory Structure Testing

This file serves as the index for the `/subdir/` path. When a client requests a directory, the server should:

1. Look for an index.gmi file in that directory
2. Serve the index file if found
3. Handle the request appropriately if no index exists

## Navigation

=> /index.gmi Back to main index
=> ../test.gmi Up to parent directory files

## Purpose

This subdirectory tests:
* Directory traversal
* Index file serving
* Relative path handling
* Directory-based content organization

The empty-dir/ directory (sibling to this subdir) contains no index file to test how the server handles empty directories.